    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The AIDOC concept explicitly states it's *derived from* prov:Agent (which is what mex-core uses). The descriptions are highly aligned – both refer to agents. While AIDOC specifies 'AI lifecycle', this doesn’t fundamentally change the core meaning of ‘agent’ in this context; it simply adds a domain restriction.  The lexical similarity score supports a strong relationship."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AIAgent ;
    align:target <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#Agent> .

